bcl:definition.bcl:text:
automation-enabled device means a device that, when installed on the
authority's electric system, is capable of being used by the authority, at a location
remote from the device, to control the flow of electricity;

electric distribution system means the equipment of the authority that
is energized at less than 60 kilovolts and is used by the authority to provide electricity
at less than 60 kilovolts;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
transmitting information in digital form to and receiving information in digital
            form from a smart meter with which the authority has established a secure
            telecommunications link;

bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
communications infrastructure for transmitting information among smart meters
              and the computer hardware and software systems described in subparagraph
                (ii);

bcl:clause.bcl:text:
provide, through the internet, to a person who receives electricity from the
                authority secure access to information about the person's electricity consumption
                and generation, if any, measured by a smart meter;

bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
estimate the amount of electricity supplied from a portion of the electric
              distribution system to unmetered loads that are not known to the authority and to
              estimate the location of those loads;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
the acquisition of investigation devices and computer software to enable the
            authority to identify the location of the unmetered loads referred to in paragraph (a)
              (iv);
